<subSubSection id="C3726506B0357267C997FDF8FB68FD34" pageId="6" pageNumber="474" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD7368DB0357267C997FDF8FEFEFD8F" blockId="6.[160,1156,610,704]" box="[160,276,610,635]" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="B91CEA9FB0357267C997FDF8FEFEFD8F" bold="true" box="[160,276,610,635]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7368DB0357267C997FD1FFB68FD34" blockId="6.[160,1156,610,704]" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">
Distinguished from known congeners by distinctive filiform E (
<figureCitation id="13532A08B0357267CA58FD1FFC25FD69" box="[879,975,645,669]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1202,1225]" captionTargetBox="[177,1151,142,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-95@7.[163,1152,142,1171]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Epidius coloratus sp. nov. RMNH 15921. (a) Male palp, ventral view. (b) Same, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184391/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(a, b)), C (ovoid, curved tip, 
<figureCitation id="13532A08B0357267C815FD32FE6BFD34" box="[290,385,680,704]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1202,1225]" captionTargetBox="[177,1151,142,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-95@7.[163,1152,142,1171]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Epidius coloratus sp. nov. RMNH 15921. (a) Male palp, ventral view. (b) Same, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184391/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(a, b)), presence of a filiform MA and oval, curved RTA (
<figureCitation id="13532A08B0357267CACCFD32FBB3FD34" box="[1019,1113,680,704]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1202,1225]" captionTargetBox="[177,1151,142,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-95@7.[163,1152,142,1171]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Epidius coloratus sp. nov. RMNH 15921. (a) Male palp, ventral view. (b) Same, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184391/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(a)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3726506B0357267C997FD77FD1FFCDC" box="[160,757,749,808]" pageId="6" pageNumber="474" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD7368DB0357267C997FD77FEF7FCF2" blockId="6.[160,757,749,808]" box="[160,285,749,774]" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="B91CEA9FB0357267C997FD77FEF7FCF2" bold="true" box="[160,285,749,774]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7368DB0357267C997FC8AFD1FFCDC" blockId="6.[160,757,749,808]" box="[160,757,784,808]" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">
Refers to the intense golden colour of the 
<typeStatus id="54D3882FB0357267CBBDFC8AFD1BFCDC" box="[650,753,784,808]" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3726506B0357267C997FCCFFE95FB3C" pageId="6" pageNumber="474" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD7368DB0357267C997FCCFFECCFC9A" blockId="6.[160,1156,853,1155]" box="[160,294,853,878]" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="B91CEA9FB0357267C997FCCFFECCFC9A" bold="true" box="[160,294,853,878]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7368DB0357267C997FCEDFCD5FB77" blockId="6.[160,1156,853,1155]" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="B91CEA9FB0357267C997FCEDFF3EFC64" box="[160,212,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">Male</emphasis>
. Total length: 3.6; prosoma length: 1.8, width: 1.5. Leg I: femur 2.5, patella 0.9, tibia 2.4, metatarsus 2.1, tarsus 0.9. Prosoma dark yellow, eye regions darker, without prominent markings or conspicuous setae. Opisthosoma without spots or markings, folium absent. Leg formula 1243, ALE&gt; PLE&gt; PME&gt; AME. AER, PER recurved, eyes on brown-coloured mounds, but not touching. Palps as in 
<figureCitation id="13532A08B0357267CB50FB99FD2FFBEF" box="[615,709,1027,1051]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1202,1225]" captionTargetBox="[177,1151,142,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-95@7.[163,1152,142,1171]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Epidius coloratus sp. nov. RMNH 15921. (a) Male palp, ventral view. (b) Same, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184391/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(a, b), femur and tibia characteristically elongated, femur as long as tibia, furnished with 6 thick spines and MTr. RTA present, ovoid, curved. Bulbus ovoid. C ovate, curved tip surrounds E. MA present in between C and tegulum. Embolus broad based, filiform (
<figureCitation id="13532A08B0357267CBAAFBF1FD13FB77" box="[669,761,1131,1155]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1202,1225]" captionTargetBox="[177,1151,142,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-95@7.[163,1152,142,1171]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Epidius coloratus sp. nov. RMNH 15921. (a) Male palp, ventral view. (b) Same, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184391/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(a, b)).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD7368DB0357267C997FB35FE95FB3C" blockId="6.[160,383,1199,1224]" box="[160,383,1199,1224]" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="B91CEA9FB0357267C997FB35FF16FB3C" bold="true" box="[160,252,1199,1224]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
